The paper presents a method for adapting a single neural network to multiple tasks, which is a common problem in machine learning. The approach involves learning binary masks that piggyback on an existing network, which is related to network quantization and pruning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of end-to-end differentiable learning, which is a common technique in neural networks and could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on classification tasks, which could place it in cs.CL (Computation and Language).
